descriptions: I am an assistant professor at University of Kansas. Before that I was a research staff member at IBM research working on AI for healthcare. I received my Ph.D. in Information Technology from Rutgers University in 2018. My research interests include data mining and its broad range of applications on health informatics, mobile intelligence, and natural language processing.
